Not quite sure what the motivation was for this.  Of course it aims at f7, which is always a good idea, and it supports the QN moving to d5 but I could have achieved that by 5. Bxc6 Nxc6 or, if Black recaptured on c6 with a pawn, left Black with doubled pawns.
